# Banking api

A secure, scalable banking API designed to demonstrate best practices in transaction handling, authentication, and API architecture. Built to solve the challenge of concurrent money transfers using ACID-compliant database transactions."


## Features

- User authentication (JWT)
- Saving of refresh and access token in http only cookie
- Account management
- Secure password hashing
- I implemented Prisma transactions for money transfers to ensure atomicity, preventing the 'lost update' problem.
- Integrated Redis with express-rate-limit to prevent brute-force attacks on the /login and /transfer endpoints.

## Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express
- TypeScript
- Prisma ORM
- PostgreSQL
- Jest & Supertest (testing)
- ioredis for cache
- resend from email
- redis and express-rate-limit for rate limiting


## Installation

1. Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Emmylyn2025/Typescript-Express
cd the_api

2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install

3. Database configuration

DATABASE_URL=your_database_url
JWT_SECRET=your_secret

4. Run the migration

```bash
npx prisma migrate dev
npx prisma generate



