# 📡 5. API Endpoints

```md
## API Endpoints

### Auth
POST /banking/register  
GET  /banking/verify-email
POST /banking/login  
POST /banking/logout
POST /banking/refresh
POST /banking/forgot-password
POST /banking/reset-password/:token

### Users
GET /banking/users
GET /banking/users?name=emmanuel  ##filter by name
GET /banking/users?email=emmanuel@gmail.com ##filter by email
GET /banking/users?role=admin ##filter by role
GET /banking/users?id=12344 ## filter by id
GET /banking/users?sort=-name&limit=5 ##Sort by name(desending) with limit 5
GET /banking/users?sort=-email&limit=6 ##Sort by email(desending) with limit 6
GET /banking/users?sort=-createdAt&limit=6 ##Sort by the(desending) time they registered with limit 6
GET /banking/users?sort=name&limit=5 ##Sort by name(asending) with limit 5
GET /banking/users?sort=email&limit=6 ##Sort by email(asending) with limit 6
GET /banking/users?sort=createdAt&limit=6 ##Sort by the time(asending) they registered with limit 6
GET /banking/users?sort=createdAt&limit=6&page=2 ##Sort by the time(asending) they registered with limit 6 and offset of 2
GET /banking/users?name[ilike]=Emma ##If you want to filter names that include the letters "Emma"
GET /banking/users/:id ## Get a single user by id
DELETE /banking/:userId
PATCH /banking/:userId  

### Account
GET /banking/account  
POST /banking/transfer
GET /banking/transfer ## Fetch all the transfer
GET /banking/transfer?amount=4000 ## Fetch the transfer that the amount is 4000
GET /banking/transfer?amount[gte]=4000 ## Fetch the transfer that the amount is 4000 or greater than 4000
GET /banking/transfer?amount[lte]=4000 ## Fetch the transfer that the amount is 4000 or less than 4000
GET /banking/transfer?amount[lt]=4000  ## Fetch the transfer that the amount is less than 4000
GET /banking/transfer?amount[gt]=4000  ## Fetch the transfer that the amount is greater than 4000
GET /banking/transfer/:id ## Get a single transfer by id



## Example: Login

### Request

POST /banking/login

```json
{
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Response
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Login successful",
  "data": access_token
}

###The access token will be saved in cookie

## Example: Register

### Request

POST /banking/register

```json
{
  "name": "test",
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Response
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Registration successful, email verification ahs been sant to you email",
  "data": user_data
}


## Environment Variables

- DATABASE_URL
- JWT_SECRET
- PORT
